                            <comment id="15193942" author="shils" created="Mon, 14 Mar 2016 19:14:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This occurs because &apos;implicitThis&apos; is not set correctly in Newify transformed method calls. A simpler example:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;A {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; foo() { &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;abc&apos;&lt;/span&gt; }
}

@groovy.transform.CompileStatic
@groovy.lang.Newify
&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; test(A arg) {
    Closure&amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt; cl = { A it -&amp;gt; it.foo() }
    cl.call(arg)
}

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;assert&lt;/span&gt; test(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; A()) == &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;abc&apos;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The above fails with the same error (and for the same reason) as the example in the issue description.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
